m de Weeks III于1403年出生在英国英格兰戴文宏尼其。他和Mary Williamson至少有1个儿子。他去世于1480年3月31日在他的家乡享年77岁。"},"hr":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403.–31. ožujka 1480.","1405–1430":"1405–1430.","1425–1483":"1425.–1483","1403–1480":"1403.–1480","1403":"1403.","1425":"1425.","1430":"1430.","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31. ožujka 1480.","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England, UK":"Honeychurch, Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom","England":"England","Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honeychurch, Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403–31. března 1480","1405–1430":"1405–1430","1425–1483":"1425–1483","1403–1480":"1403–1480","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1430":"1430","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31. března 1480","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England, UK":"Honeychurch, Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom","England":"Anglie","Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honeychurch, Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403–31. marts 1480","1405–1430":"1405–1430","1425–1483":"1425–1483","1403–1480":"1403–1480","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1430":"1430","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31. marts 1480","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England, UK":"Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403–31 maart 1480","1405–1430":"1405–1430","1425–1483":"1425–1483","1403–1480":"1403–1480","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1430":"1430","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31 maart 1480","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England, UK":"Honeychurch, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honeychurch, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403–31 March 1480","1405–1430":"1405–1430","1425–1483":"1425–1483","1403–1480":"1403–1480","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1430":"1430","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31 March 1480","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England, UK":"Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"FitzWilliam","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (of Norman origin): from Anglo-Norman French <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name   William  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Weeks","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Wicks  .","Americanized form of Norwegian and Swedish   Vik  .","History: This surname was brought to North America independently by several different bearers in the 17th and 18th centuries. One of the earliest on record is Leonard Weeks, who emigrated from Somerset, England, to Portsmouth, NH, some time before 1656. — William Weeks, recorded in Edgartown, Martha's Vineyard, MA, from 1653 onward, was probably a cousin or other relative of the John Wickes mentioned at   Wickes  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Wicks","meanings":["English (southern England and East Anglia): generally a variant of   Wick  ,   Wyke  , or the obsolete form <b>Week</b>, with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. Occasionally from the plural form of Middle English <i>wik(e)</i>, late Middle English <i>weke</i> ‘building, especially one where dairy products are made’ (compare   Wick  ). An alternative Middle English plural form occurs in   Wicken  ."]},{"name":"Weekes","meanings":["English: variant of   Weeks   or   Wicks  . This form of the surname is frequent in Barbados."]},{"name":"Vik","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Alf, Erik, Lars, Lennart, Nels, Nils.","Norwegian and Swedish: habitational name from any of numerous farmsteads all over Norway and Sweden, so named with Old Norse <i>vík</i> ‘small bay, inlet’. In Swedish it may also be a topographic or ornamental name. Compare   Weeks  .","Czech: from a short form of the personal name <i>Viktor</i> (see   Victor  )."]}]},{"name":"LORD","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Lorraine   or variant spelling of   Laurie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lorraine","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin denoting a migrant from the province of <i>Lorraine</i> in eastern France. This derives its name from Latin <i>Lotharingia</i> ‘territory of the people of <i>Lothar</i>’. The latter is a Germanic personal name derived from <i>hlud</i> ‘fame’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. <i>Lorraine</i> began to be used as a girl's name in Scotland in the 19th century, and for a time in the second half of the 20th century enjoyed great popularity, which has since waned."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"LORD William FitzWilliam de Weeks III was born in 1403, in Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mary Williamson. He died on 31 March 1480, in his hometown, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403–31. märts 1480","1405–1430":"1405–1430","1425–1483":"1425–1483","1403–1480":"1403–1480","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1430":"1430","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31. märts 1480","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England, UK":"Honeychurch, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Honeychurch, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honeychurch, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1403–31 March 1480":"1403–31. maaliskuuta 1480","1405–1430":"1405–1430","1425–1483":"1425–1483","1403–1480":"1403–1480","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1430":"1430","1483":"1483","1480":"1480","31 March 1480":"31. maaliskuuta 1480","1405":"1405","Honeychurch, Devon, Devonshire, England